线段树

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
#define int long long
#define Dg(n)  cout<<n<<" ";
#define F(n) for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
#define F1(n) for(int i=n;i>=1;i--)
#define F2(n,s) for(int i=1;i<=n;i+=s)

const int INF=0x3f3f3f3f;
const int LXB=1e6+10;
                                 
int n,m,k,l,ans;
int tree[LXB<<2],num[LXB],add[LXB<<2];

// int le[LXB],ri[LXB];
void pup(int rt){tree[rt]=tree[rt<<1]+tree[rt<<1|1];}

void build(int l,int r,int rt){
    if(l==r){tree[rt]=num[l];return;}
    int m=(l+r)/2;
    build(l,m,rt<<1);
    build(m+1,r,rt<<1|1);
    pup(rt);
}

// void up(int l1,int l,int r,int rt,int x){
    // if(l==r){tree[rt]+=x;return ;}
    // int m=(l+r)/2;
    // if(l1<=m)up(l1,l,m,rt<<1,x);
    // else     up(l1,m,r,rt<<1|1,x);
    // pup(rt);
// }
// 
void pdown(int ln,int rn,int rt){
    if(add[rt]){
        add[rt<<1]+=add[rt];
        add[rt<<1|1]+=add[rt];
        tree[rt<<1]+=add[rt]*ln;
        tree[rt<<1|1]+=add[rt]*rn;
        add[rt]=0;
    }
}

void up(int l1,int r1,int l,int r,int rt,int x){
    if(l1<=l and r<=r1){
        tree[rt]+=x*(r-l+1);
        add[rt]+=x;
        return;
    }
    int m=(l+r)/2;
    pdown(m-l+1,r-m,rt);
    if(l1<=m)up(l1,r1,l,m,rt<<1,x);
    if(r1>m)up(l1,r1,m+1,r,rt<<1|1,x);
    pup(rt);
}

int out(int l1,int r1,int l,int r,int rt){
    if(l1<=l and r<=r1){
        return tree[rt];
    }
    int m=(l+r)/2;
    pdown(m-l+1,r-m,rt);
    int ans=0;
    if(l1<=m)ans+=out(l1,r1,l,m,rt<<1);
    if(r1> m)ans+=out(l1,r1,m+1,r,rt<<1|1);
    return ans;
}

signed main(){
    ios::sync_with_stdio(0); cin.tie(0);
    cin>>n>>m;
    
    return 0;
}

Welcome to [Hexo](https://hexo.io/)! This is your very first post. Check [documentation](https://hexo.io/docs/) for more info. If you get any problems when using Hexo, you can find the answer in [troubleshooting](https://hexo.io/docs/troubleshooting.html) or you can ask me on [GitHub](https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues).

## Quick Start

### Create a new post

``` bash
$ hexo new "My New Post"
```

More info: [Writing](https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html)

### Run server

``` bash
$ hexo server
```

More info: [Server](https://hexo.io/docs/server.html)

### Generate static files

``` bash
$ hexo generate
```

More info: [Generating](https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html)

### Deploy to remote sites

``` bash
$ hexo deploy
```

More info: [Deployment](https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html)
